00:00:08.751 --> 00:00:10.539
inertial frame of reference,

00:00:10.539 --> 00:00:11.625
and so I am,

00:00:11.625 --> 00:00:14.506
I am in an inertial frame
of reference myself,

00:00:14.506 --> 00:00:16.233
and in fact I'm going to define

00:00:16.233 --> 00:00:17.762
my frame of reference by me,

00:00:17.762 --> 00:00:19.142
I'm gonna say I'm at the origin

00:00:19.142 --> 00:00:20.869
of my frame of reference.

00:00:20.869 --> 00:00:22.374
So at all times,

00:00:22.374 --> 00:00:25.237
I consider myself to be stationary,

00:00:25.237 --> 00:00:26.640
and I am at the point,

00:00:26.640 --> 00:00:28.520
'x' equals zero,

00:00:28.520 --> 00:00:29.641
and we're gonna focus on

00:00:29.641 --> 00:00:30.848
just the 'x' dimension,

00:00:30.848 --> 00:00:32.142
to simplify our discussion,

00:00:32.142 --> 00:00:33.136
and I have, you know,

00:00:33.136 --> 00:00:34.274
my oxygen and everything,

00:00:34.274 --> 00:00:35.165
and food,

00:00:35.165 --> 00:00:38.725
so no need to worry about me.

00:00:38.725 --> 00:00:40.356
Now, what I've drawn here

00:00:40.356 --> 00:00:42.145
are some axes,

00:00:42.145 --> 00:00:45.209
so that I can plot the path of things

00:00:45.209 --> 00:00:47.016
as time progresses

00:00:47.016 --> 00:00:49.760
in my frame of reference.

00:00:49.760 --> 00:00:50.877
And one thing that

00:00:50.877 --> 00:00:52.136
many of ya'll might have noticed

00:00:52.136 --> 00:00:54.108
is that I have plotted time in seconds

00:00:54.108 --> 00:00:55.510
on the vertical axis,

00:00:55.510 --> 00:00:57.418
